quickshell for Debian
----------------------

This is the Debian package of quickshell, a QtQuick-based desktop shell toolkit
for Wayland and X11.

Building from source
--------------------

If you need to rebuild the package with different feature flags, you can modify
debian/rules to add CMake configuration options. See BUILD.md in the source
tree for available options.

All features are enabled by default in this package. To disable specific
features, add the appropriate -D flags to the dh_auto_configure override
in debian/rules.

Configuration
-------------

Quickshell configuration files are typically placed in:
  ~/.config/quickshell/

See the upstream documentation at https://quickshell.outfoxxed.me for
configuration examples and documentation.

Debug Symbols
-------------

Debug symbols are provided in the quickshell-dbgsym package for crash
reporting and debugging purposes.

